    "problemStatement": "Chef is given a tree of **N** nodes.\nLet M denote the number of simple paths with at least two nodes.\nNotice that M = **N * (N - 1) / 2**.\n\nThere are (M * (M - 1) * (M - 2) / 6) unordered triples of such paths.\nYour task is to count how many of them are nice.\nA triple of paths (**A**, **B**, **C**) is nice if and only if **either** of the following conditions is satisfied:\n\n\nThe three paths are pairwise disjoint (no two of them share a node).\nEach pair of paths intersect with each other.\nIn other words: paths **A** and **B** share at least one node, paths **A** and **C** share at least one node, and also paths **B** and **C** share at least one node.\nOutput the number of nice triples of paths modulo (**109+7**).",
    "constraints": [
      "**1** ≤ **N** ≤ **3*105**",
      "**1** ≤ **a**i, **b**i ≤ **N**",
      "**a**i ≠ **b**i",
      "Subtasks`Subtask 1 (15 points):",
      "`",
      "**1** ≤ **N** ≤ **2000**",
      "`Subtask 2 (57 points):",
      "`",
      "**1** ≤ **N** ≤ **105**",
      "`Subtask 3 (28 points):",
      "`",
      "Original constraints.",
